3 LAYERS- structure, function and presentation

<html> tag says this is an html document. contains everything
<head> is for technical nothing inside of this will be on the page
<body> is on the visable page
<title> will be shown in the browser tab
<link> connects HTML file with accompanying files
----------------------------------------
p(selector) in the CSS window effects the P tag in HTML.
-------------
selector { property: value; }

selector defines what HTML elements our rule applies to
property is what aspect you are changing
value is the setting for that property.

-------------------------------

selector1 { 
	property1: value; 
	property2: value; 
}
selector2 { 
	property1: value; 
	property2: value; 
	property3: value;
}

you can do this endlessly

---------------------------------------------

Commmon CSS properties

color: purple or  #c857c8; -> text color
background: pink or  #f5dcf5;-> background color
font-size: 18px or  150%; ->  size of the text
font-family: sans-serif or  “Aria”; -> Typeface
margin: 50px;-> spacing outside an element
padding: 20px 50px 20px 10px;-> spacing inside an element
border: 1px dashed green; -> line around an element
width: 300px or  80%;->  how wide an element is
height: 200px or  50vh;-> how tall an element is
display: block or  inline or  flex->  layout behavior
--------------
w3schools.com/cssref/index.php (has hundreds of properties)
-------------------------------------------
CSS is very flexible

You can create your own HTML tags that you define in CSS
____---___
IDs and Classes
<p>Just an NPC paragraph nothing tp look at</p>
<p id=”main-point” >This very special element is awarder with its own ID</p>
<p class=”highlight” >This element belongs to many sharing the same class</p>
<p  id=”main-point”  class=”highlight” >Well this one have both personality and class allegiance.</p>



TAG {} Selects ALL html elements with the said tag
p{... } will address all <p>
.CLASS{} Selects ALL html elements with the said CLASS attribute
.highlight {...} will address all <p class=”highlight>...</p>

