Lecture 4 10/7/25

DIVs-> today
Every HTML element is either block or inline


An inline element flows with the text around it .
It does not start on a new line and only takes up as much width as neccessary.
<a> link tags
<span> tags
<strong> 
<em> tags

A vlock element always
starts on a new line
- takes up the full width available.

typical block elements:
<div>
<p>
<h1>
<li>




